    "body": "@luigar Thanks for opening the issue.\r\n\r\nIf I understand correctly account `A` never added the contact back, is that correct?\r\n\r\nWe only share contact information in 2 cases: \r\n\r\n1) `A` starts chatting with `B` , in that case `A` information is shared with `B`, but **not the other way around** . This is to preserve privacy of `B`, who has never acknowledge to share information.\r\n\r\n2) `A` adds `B` as a contact (or viceversa). In this case again `A`'s information will be shared with be `B`, **but not viceversa**, same reason as before, preserving `B`'s privacy who never acknowledge wanting to share information with `A`.\r\n\r\nIn your case you should see on `A`'s phone in the chat a link (`Add to contacts`), if you click on it you should see `A`'s information on `B`.\r\n\r\nIf that's not the case then it is a bug and we will look into it, otherwise let me know and I will close the issue.",
